<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-003-081 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 559 128</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Dec 3 1991 n1815* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Olivetti chief De Benedetti unravels structure left by hispredecessor.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ing. C. Olivetti e Compagnia S.p.A. (Management).andO;Topic:     Management StyleBusiness PlanningCentralizationOrganization Structure.andO;Person:    de Benedetti, Carlo (Management).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>OLIVETTI CHIEF DE BENEDETTI UNRAVELS STRUCTUREandM;LEFT BY HIS PREDECESSORandM;Within three weeks of retaking the reins at Ing C Olivetti andamp; Co SpA, Carlo deBenedetti has largely dismantled the company structure put in place threeyears ago by Vittorio Cassoni, bringing administration and finance, personneland industrial relations back into a centralised organisation, in a move thatis expected to cost 2,000 jobs but, it is hoped, will save $330m a year inoperating expenses.andP;  The present structure of Olivetti Systems andamp; Networks formainstream systems, Olivetti Office for personal computers and relatedproducts, Olivetti Technologies for components, and Olivetti InformationServices for software will disappear, with the large overlap in sales forcesto be eliminated.andP;  There will be three new units, Operations, DiversifiedActivities and Public Administration, putting a new stress on public sectorbusiness, but Information Services will survive.andP;  Elserino Piol, head ofSystems andamp; Networks, will head Operations, which covers about 90% of the totalbusiness, and will have Information Technology and Office divisions.andO;</TEXT></DOC>